description: Dunny is, was, and always will be. The Dunny Evolved Series features five artists - Frank Kozik, Kronk, Huck Gee, McBess, and Scott Tolleson - tackling the theory of Dunny evolution. Each artist delivers a series of 3 dunny designs, making 15 newly evolved 3-inch vinyl figures.

Featuring the Stick of Truth warriors Stan, Kyle, Cartman, Kenny, and Butters, embroiled in an intense live-action-role-playing game, each wielding his weapon of choice, and dressed to kill underpants gnomes, vampire kids, and hippies. From the fray, a young hero will rise, destined to be South Park’s savior.

name: Kidrobot x Simpsons Tree House of Horrors Mini Toys  by Matt Groening
description:
Hello, everyone. The following series is really scary. Featuring 12 of the wickedest Tree House of Horror characters, this special SIMPSONS series is horrifyingly fun. Each frightful figure is blind packed and guaranteed to give you that mind numbing rush of energy that is normally only possible by consuming hoards of drug store chocolate right before bed. Each Simpsons Tree House of Horrors toy figure is 3-inches and sold individually.

About Kidrobot X Artist Series:
Exploring an extensive range of themes – from ironic twists on pop culture to commentary on sexuality – Kidrobot X represents the work of graphic designers, toy artists, graffiti writers, illustrators and beyond. Dunny is Kidrobot’s most collected artist-designed “platform toy.” Dunny series and all KR art toys are carefully curated to highlight a wide breadth of style and balance.

name: Giver DIY by Andrew Bell
description:
Giver DIY 

 

Some time ago we produced a special limited edition of the Giver figures, but we weren't totally happy with the final product. Instead of tossing them into a bin, we thought it would be cool to strip them down and prime them up, ready for the growing customizing crowd! Head and wings remove easily for painting. Each figure is professionally primed with a thick white base, ready to paint or draw on.

name: CALAVERA By Humberto Ramos and Francisco Herrera
description:
CALAVERA

CALAVERA  survives in Chilangolandia, born on a tomb stone in Mixquic, in a Day of the Dead. He is CALAVERA, who, legend says, shall confront and defeat the ruthless creatures from the underworld. His father, a baker, his mother, a curandera, and his grandfather, the legendary wrestler known as LA CALACA. This is how our hero combines a bizarre mix which transforms him, maybe, into the last hope for mankind.  Along with his inseparable partner, TALAVERA, they fight the evil during weekdays while Friday and Saturday the crowds throng the arenas where they become the unquestioned kings of the ring. Calavera gains his strength from the Day of the Dead loaf and the refined sugar from the sugar skulls prepared when the duty calls by his mom, doña Remedios, with an age-old secret formula.  CALAVERA is back in the ring, thus putting an end to the rumors about his death. Thank you, dear Virgin, for sending him back, THANK YOU...

CALAVERA is the first collaboration work on a toy between Humberto Ramos and Francisco Herrera.

Size: Size: 7.5"H (19cm) x 5.1"W (13cm)

Abandoned by his biological parents in the barren deserts of Mexico, the infant Tequila was found and raised by a very caring family of desert cacti. One very sad day, his adopted parents died. After many days of crying, Tequila took his parents deceased remains and fermented them in an empty Tequila bottle. When he needs a quick boost of physical strength, Tequila empowers himself by taking a sip from this very special bottle.

standing approx. 7-8 inches tall, "bronze" colorway and limited to only 100-pcs worldwide with very few having survived with there wing unharmed,,,this one has his wings :) and they are perfect!

Made from stone resin and weighing in at just under 5 pounds!!! (4.95lb) (for reference, an average 8" dunny weighs 1/2lb)

he does have marks on the top of his head,,,but i never saw one that did not have these shipping marks,

this is one of Huck Gee's rarest pieces,,,here is your chace,

Why PUTO? Huck says: "It's a play on words, a mix up of Spanish slang, old Italian and Philippino. In Italian "Putto" is the name of the cute little babies with wings that showed up in renaissance period paintings. "Puto" is Spanish for male prostitute/bitch. And in the Philippines PUTO is a cute white dessert, a tasty filipino steamed rice cake and is very, very popular. Yum." = *yumz indeed!*

name: Junko Mizun Kuro Megami Kidrobot Black Figure
description: the 11" goddess cast in black vinyl with gold accents and accompanied by two clear, winged guardians. True to Junko's art, Kuro Megami is darkly seductive. True to the Kidrobot Black concept, the figure's strong sculpt carries the design with detailed elements throughout from the numerous flowers flowing across her body to her heavily textured hair.

name: Banksy You Are An Acceptable Level of Threat
description:
Compiled by Gary Shove and Patrick Potter

The locations are from around the world (predominantly the UK, US and Europe), and many images have never been seen before. When Banksy started out painting, the political landscape was bleak. Fortunately now, it's ten times worse.

 

As Banksy's cheerfully aggressive political work becomes ever more relevant, this comprehensive tome sets about presenting his art in the context of the era he was responding to.

 
228 pages, Hardcover, 8 3/4'' x 10 1/4'' ( 210 x 270 mm)
250 color illustrations, English
